Russians warned about fake calls from banks
In Russia, the number of calls from fraudsters who replace the phone number of the bank has increased.
This is reported by “Kommersant” with reference to data of the Central Bank.
In the summer of 2019, the regulator gave information to telecom operators about more than 2.5 thousand numbers from which customers of various financial organizations called.
In 189 cases, operators found a change of number.
Another 218 numbers were blocked, and in 59 cases, restrictions were imposed on the use of financial services.
Deputy head of the Department of information security of the Central Bank Artem Sychev said that a wide range of Russian banks faced with the substitution of the number.
He explained that operators do not always respond to warnings of the Central Bank about fraudulent calls, citing the absence of such an obligation in the law "On Communications".
Otkritie Bank, Rosbank and Alfa-Bank confirmed the information about the increase in the number of fraudulent calls with a change of number.
As reported in the press service of “Beeline”, some of the information about fraudulent calls, which was passed by the Central Bank, was incorrect: the lists included numbers that are really used by banks to communicate with customers.
Their blocking would lead to failures in the work of the organization.
Artem Sychev said that the Central Bank plans to create a database of numbers of fraudsters, which the operator will contact at each call to check the number.
He explained that in order to create such a base, amendments to the legislation would be required.
