Deliveries of “sanctions” to Russia fell 100 times
The Russian government has estimated that the supply of agricultural products and food to Russia from countries that fell under the Russian food embargo has decreased by more than 100 times since 2013.
According to the report sent to Russian President Vladimir Putin, in the first half of 2019, 31 thousand tons of products were imported from sanctions countries against 3 million 442.2 thousand tons for the same period of 2013.
At the same time, the cost of imported products decreased to $ 226.5 million from $ 4 billion 975.5 million, respectively.
We are talking about the supply of goods that are not subject to the embargo.
As indicated in the report, the volumes of prohibited imports were compensated by an increase in imports from the CIS countries, Africa, South-East Asia, Serbia.
Recall that at the end of August, the government extended until December 31, 2020 the validity of the rules for the destruction of agricultural products, raw materials and food, which are prohibited for import to Russia under counter-sanctions.
In the document posted on the official portal of legal information, it was noted that the rules have been extended for another year - from December 31, 2019 to December 31, 2020.
Initially, the decree on the destruction of the sanction applied to products from the United States, the EU, Australia, Norway and Canada.
Later, from August 13, 2015, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland, Liechtenstein joined this list, from January 1, 2016 - Ukraine.
The decree signed by Putin on the destruction of illegally imported into the country “sanctions” (products that fell under the food embargo, which Moscow imposed in response to anti-Russian sanctions of the West) came into force in 2015.
In turn, the government allowed the destruction of “sanctioned” food in any legal way.
As Western sanctions have continued, the Russian Federation has also extended its retaliatory measures.
At the same time, this measure does not apply to products that citizens import for personal use.
The ban does not apply to the import of goods for personal consumption weighing up to 5 kilograms.
However, the head of the Presidential Council for the Development of Civil Society and Human Rights Mikhail Fedotov earlier called the destruction of food “simply immoral”, and this, according to him, negatively affects the education of people.
Moreover, the initiative to ban the destruction of food suitable for consumption, in early June, was made by Rospotrebnadzor.
After that, a similar recommendation to the government was made by the Human Rights Council under the President of the Russian Federation.
And Deputy Prime Minister Alexei Gordeev said that it is wrong to destroy food, and we need to think about how to use them for their intended purpose, assessing the quality.
The head of the company was found guilty of tax evasion
By the verdict of the Leninsky District Court of the city of Cheboksary, Vyacheslav Morozov, the director of Land and Law LLC, was found guilty of committing crimes under part 2 b of article 199 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (evading taxes from the organization by including deliberately false information in the tax declaration, committed on an especially large scale) and part 2 of article 327 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation (forging its official document).
This is reported by the press service of the investigative Department of the TFR on Chuvashia.
From January 2008 to December 2009, Vyacheslav Morozov entered information on imperfect transactions in the tax accounting documents of LLC.
According to fictitious documents, the company incurred additional costs, and, consequently, the amount of taxes payable on value added and on the profit of the organization was reduced by 11.2 million rubles.
Vyacheslav Morozov was sentenced to 3.5 years of probation.
By 2023, the first school of a new format will open in the center of the capital
The school of a new sample will be opened in Khamovniki.
According to the head of Moskomstroyinvest Anastasia Pyatova, there will create all the conditions for self-realization and development of children’s talents.
The educational institution decided to call the "New Look".
This project will be supervised by the Moscow State Institute of International Relations of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Russia and the Foundation for Economic Development of Higher Education.
The design of the building with an area of about 10 thousand "squares" is planned to begin next year.
Will finish construction at the end of 2022, and in the next will begin to recruit the first students.
"The project provides for the creation of a public, non-profit educational space, which will be based on the traditions of the classical Moscow school and experimental methods," the press service of Moskomstroyinvest said.
In Chile began to build a telescope worth 1 billion euros
This is reported by TASS with reference to the press service of the European Southern Observatory (ESO).
The construction of the dome of the building, where the E-ELT (European Extremely Large Telescope) telescope will be located, has officially begun this week, so far the most expensive and ambitious ground-based astronomical project.
Its total value, according to ESO, will exceed one billion euros.
Most of this money will be spent on the manufacture of equipment and the construction of the observatory building.
The most expensive and complex component of the telescope is its record-breaking large mirror, whose diameter will be about 39 meters.
It will be assembled from 798 hexagonal segments measuring 1.4 meters.
This huge mirror, as well as two auxiliary reflective surfaces with a diameter of 4.2 and 3.75 meters, will help E-ELT to get the first detailed photos of planets outside the solar system, stars in other galaxies, and also look for Earth’s twins.
In addition, scientists will try to use this observatory to observe the surroundings of Sgr A*, a supermassive black hole at the center of the Milky Way.
Despite the fact that the construction of the dome has just begun, scientists, engineers and other specialists have been developing mirrors, scientific instruments and other components of the observatory for three years - since the announcement of the first plans for the construction of the E-ELT.
The contract for the production of the main mirror, whose total cost was about 400 million euros, was awarded to the German company SCHOTT and the French company Safran Reosc.
